<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FFB8EF7BFF42FF0FFDFBFE14" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB8EF7BFF42FF0FFD1CFE30" blockId="16.[151,1437,149,429]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB8EF7BFF42FF0FFEE7FF6C" bold="true" box="[199,338,186,212]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Comments:</emphasis>
In addition to providing the first record of the species since its original description, we recorded males for the first time. In the same way as the two previous species, 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB8EF7BFC1AFF6AFB8FFF40" baseAuthorityName="Redtenbacher" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[927,1082,222,248]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Neoconocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavirostris">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB8EF7BFC1AFF6AFB8FFF40" box="[927,1082,222,248]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">N. flavirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents colour polymorphism, with light green and yellowish/brown individuals. We also highlight that in this species the vertex is almost as long as the length of the pronotal disc. This was one of the few species of 
<taxonomicName id="9AC477E8FFB8EF7BFC29FE93FBC6FEF8" authorityName="Karny" authorityYear="1907" box="[940,1139,294,320]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" genus="Neoconocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB8EF7BFC29FE93FBC6FEF8" box="[940,1139,294,320]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Neoconocephalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for which we could make a reliable sex association, partly because the description was based on a female and mainly for the existing colour contrast in the body of both males and females.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFFB8EF7BFF42FE27FDFBFE14" blockId="16.[151,1437,149,429]" box="[199,590,402,429]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FFB8EF7BFF42FE27FED1FE14" bold="true" box="[199,356,402,428]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Bioacoustics:</emphasis>
Sound not recorded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
